= Introduction

== Purpose

This Software Test Guide (STG) describes the testing strategy, test organization, execution procedures, and maintenance guidance for the *Functional* library.

== Scope

This document covers:
- test categories and their purposes,
- test directory structure and naming conventions,
- test framework usage,
- test execution commands,
- traceability between requirements and tests, and
- guidelines for writing new tests.

== References

- Software Requirements Specification (SRS).
- Software Design Specification (SDS).

= Test Strategy

== Test Categories

#table(
  columns: (auto, auto, 1fr, auto),
  table.header([*Category*], [*Location*], [*Purpose*], [*Target*]),
  [Unit Tests], [`test/unit/`], [Test individual packages in isolation.], [≥ 90% coverage],
